        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:11PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hazen, or near Lahontan Reservoir, moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lahontan Reservoir, Fernley, Hazen, Junction U.S 50 And NV 117
(sheckler Cutoff), and Us 50 At Lyon-Churchill Co Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
